# Allow-list packaging: deny everything, then re-include only what ships.
#
# Why allow-list? A deny-list misses new junk the moment someone adds a new
# directory at the repo root (e.g. .idea/ from JetBrains, docs/investigations/
# from a writeup). With an allow-list, anything new is excluded by default and
# a human has to consciously opt it in.
#
# vsce uses minimatch (NOT gitignore) semantics, so `!editors/vscode/` does not
# transitively un-ignore the directory's contents. Whitelist concrete files
# (or `dir/**`) instead of bare directories.
#
# vsce auto-includes package.json, LICENSE, README.md and CHANGELOG.md, so
# they do not appear below. Everything else MUST be whitelisted explicitly or
# it will NOT be in the .vsix.

**

# Marketplace metadata. vsce special-cases package.json + README.md so they
# bypass `**`, but LICENSE and CHANGELOG.md get filtered like any other file
# and must be whitelisted explicitly.
!LICENSE
!CHANGELOG.md

# Runtime: esbuild bundles + bundled JSON schemas (loaded by the server at
# runtime — see src/server/components.ts resolveSchemasBase).
!dist/extension/extension.js
!dist/server/server.js
!dist/schemas/**

# TextMate grammars (referenced by package.json#contributes.grammars).
!syntaxes/*.json

# Language configuration (referenced by package.json#contributes.languages).
!editors/vscode/language-configuration.json

# Extension icon (referenced by package.json#icon).
!docs/assets/otel-logo.png

# Never ship source maps, even if a future allow-rule would otherwise catch
# them. Deny rules after allow-rules win.
**/*.map
